The paper discusses the challenges of enabling control-flow integrity (CFI) on microcontroller-based IoT devices, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). It also mentions the use of TrustZone-M security extensions introduced in the ARMv8-M architecture, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.EM) and system-level design and implementation (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed scheme on a Cortex-M Prototyping System, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
